exercise:
Explain how to find the following for the function f(x)={{function}}.
The open intervals where f(x) is increasing or decreasing.
The relative extrema of f(x).
{{#increasing}}
The function increases on (-\infty,{{a}}), decreases on ({{a}},{{b}}), and increases on ({{b}},\infty).
The point (x,y)=({{a}},{{fa}}) is a relative maximum, and the point (x,y)=({{b}},{{fb}}) is a relative minimum.
{{/increasing}} {{#decreasing}}
The function decreases on (-\infty,{{a}}), increases on ({{a}},{{b}}), and decreases on ({{b}},\infty).
The point (x,y)=({{a}},{{fa}}) is a relative minimum, and the point (x,y)=({{b}},{{fb}}) is a relative maximum.
{{/decreasing}}
